ZME Utilities

Custom Alias

This CRC custom alias adds some helpers like getting navaid or callsign pronunciation

  • .val [Click aircraft] - Attempt to validate a flight plan for the selected aircraft
  • .rof [Click aircraft] - Opens GCMap with departure/arrival
  • .roffa [Click aircraft] - Opens FlightAware with departure/arrival
  • .nav[navaid abbreviation] or .nav[navaid name]- Sends a PM with info (e.g. .navMEM or .navMEMPHIS)
  • .id[callsign-3LD] - Sends a PM with info about the callsign (e.g. .idFDX)
  • .acInfo[aircraft type] - Sends a PM with info about the aircraft (e.g. .acinfoB738)
  • .apt[apt] - Sends a PM with info about the airport (e.g. .aptMEM)
Download this alias

Route Validator

The route validator will show details for the flight and will attempts to pull in data from the VATSIM feed for the selected aircraft to validate based on ZME standards. The page will also try to determine the initial waypoint from the ZME reference card if enough information is available. Links to charts will require Navigraph.

  • ALL - Altitide valid for direction of flight
  • Memphis - Time restricted SIDs
  • Memphis - JET routes
